HEADWORD: Pragmatize
<hw>Prag"ma*tize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To consider,
represent, or embody (something unreal) as fact; to materialize.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>pragmatized</xex> metaphor.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Tylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prairial</ent>⟦br⟧
